 discipline and m a sympathy and understanding which can derive only from deep religious faith.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aChurch historyyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 4aReligious Studies. 7aRELIGION / Christian Church / History.2bisacsh1 aWhiting Fox, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150174114240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501741142423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501741142/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK